{"TopicId":204404,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.12.x] Alarm Enhancements 1.0.2 (26/08/2021) - Automatic Alarms and Better Naming of Alarms","CreatedByName":"severedsolo","CreatedById":80345,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-17T18:46:15Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"severedsolo","CreatedById":80345,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-17T18:46:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EAlarm Enhancements \u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis mod adds some functionality which the Stock Alarm Clock lacks but was present in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nAutomatically adds alarms for Maneuver Nodes, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E changes, and entering an atmosphere.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nRenames Manual Alarms to the active vessels name (so you don\u0027t have to remember which vessel this \u0022Periapsis Alarm\u0022 you set and forgot to change the name of is for).\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nFully configurable through the Difficulty Settings.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ELicense: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://mit-license.org/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMIT\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ESource: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/severedsolo/AlarmEnhancements\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EGithub\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EDownload: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/severedsolo/AlarmEnhancements/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EGithub\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo pics, no clicks? I don\u0027t care. There really isn\u0027t much to show you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EKnown Issues:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t always remove alarms when they are no longer applicable. This is by design. I\u0027ve noticed a stock bug where \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E changes can disappear at high timewarp, and I was having problems recognising whether a Maneuver Alarm was for the Maneuver I was trying to set it for or not. Where we can\u0027t be absolutely 100% certain an Alarm can be removed the mod will err on the side of caution.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E: \u003C/strong\u003ENow Available.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr?cmd=_s-xclick\u0026amp;hosted_button_id=2TG53K4E3PUEU\u0026amp;source=ur\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Donate to my coffee fund\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002222.00\u0022 height=\u002222\u0022 style=\u0022width:100px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u0022100\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/OO5d907.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.patreon.com/severedsolo\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022downloads_wordmark_navy@2x.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002248.34\u0022 height=\u0022320\u0022 width=\u0022662\u0022 src=\u0022https://c5.patreon.com/external/logo/downloads_wordmark_navy@2x.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-08-26T05:50:27Z\u0022 title=\u002208/26/2021 05:50  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 26, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by severedsolo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerminator K-100","CreatedById":204357,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-18T02:55:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirst!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo pics no cliks, sorry thems the rules\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nkidding, this mod looks super cool! Can\u0027t wait to try it!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"severedsolo","CreatedById":80345,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-18T13:29:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello everyone, I\u0027ve just released Alarm Enhancements 1.0.1 which fixes a few questionable decisions the mod was making.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nInformed the mod it\u0027s perfectly safe to remove Maneuver Alarms if the vessel doesn\u0027t actually have any maneuvers.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nInformed the mod it\u0027s perfectly safe to remove Atmospheric Reentry Alarms when the vessels orbit does not actually intersect the atmosphere.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nMod will now remove \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E Alarms if it can\u0027t detect an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E change AND the timewarp rate is 1x\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-08-18T17:57:22Z\u0022 title=\u002208/18/2021 05:57  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 18, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by severedsolo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"J3ansley","CreatedById":113709,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-18T16:06:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you so much for this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Phil deCube","CreatedById":120897,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-18T20:48:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat. I was sad that these things were missing from the stock clock. Thanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"flart","CreatedById":181486,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-18T21:44:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it possible not to rename alarm after creation, but to change default title in the \u0022add alarm\u0022 window ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002268747470733a2f2f692e696d6775722e636f6d2f\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022123.62\u0022 height=\u0022471\u0022 width=\u0022381\u0022 src=\u0022https://camo.githubusercontent.com/5e00683c8b6696fd4ea0b83e49e5fed4617e6636d10293e422eca6ded9beaacd/68747470733a2f2f692e696d6775722e636f6d2f4f574e6337334c2e6a706567\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"severedsolo","CreatedById":80345,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-18T21:54:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224021632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204404\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221629323088\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181486\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022flart\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, flart said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it possible not to rename alarm after creation, but to change default title in the \u0022add alarm\u0022 window ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://camo.githubusercontent.com/5e00683c8b6696fd4ea0b83e49e5fed4617e6636d10293e422eca6ded9beaacd/68747470733a2f2f692e696d6775722e636f6d2f4f574e6337334c2e6a706567\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u002268747470733a2f2f692e696d6775722e636f6d2f\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022123.62\u0022 height=\u0022471\u0022 width=\u0022381\u0022 src=\u0022https://camo.githubusercontent.com/5e00683c8b6696fd4ea0b83e49e5fed4617e6636d10293e422eca6ded9beaacd/68747470733a2f2f692e696d6775722e636f6d2f4f574e6337334c2e6a706567\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can add that - the auto-renamer can be turned off in the difficulty settings. It\u0027s late and I\u0027m about to go to bed, but I\u0027ll pick it up tomorrow if I get time (or the weekend at the latest).\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nJust to clarify (I\u0027m assuming yes, but let\u0027s be thorough), do you want to be able to set the default name of the auto-alarms as well as manual ones? Raised \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/severedsolo/AlarmEnhancements/issues/1\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E#1\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: I\u0027ve just realised what you meant. I\u0027m not sure I can mess with the default names for manual alarms but I will have a dig and see what I can do. I can definitely let you choose your own name for the auto renamer though\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-08-18T22:02:46Z\u0022 title=\u002208/18/2021 10:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 18, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by severedsolo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"flart","CreatedById":181486,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-18T22:05:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224021634\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204404\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221629323648\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002280345\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022severedsolo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, severedsolo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndo you want to be able to set the default name of the auto-alarms as well as manual ones?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes. Also ability to modify modded text to something like\u00A0\u0022maneuver for \u0026lt;\u0026lt;1\u0026gt;\u0026gt;\u0022 (as it was in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E)\u00A0 would be cool, probably using localization support.\u003Cbr\u003E\nDefault setting as \u0022\u0026lt;\u0026lt;1\u0026gt;\u0026gt;\u0022\u00A0is ok.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KraterKreator","CreatedById":150238,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-20T03:02:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you,\u00A0 \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/80345-severedsolo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002280345\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/80345-severedsolo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@severedsolo\u003C/a\u003E!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI stopped trying to move my game from 1.9.1 to 1.12.2 because these functions were missing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-08-20T03:03:46Z\u0022 title=\u002208/20/2021 03:03  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 20, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by KraterKreator\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Etypo\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Apricot","CreatedById":210807,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-20T07:35:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis mod makes my in-game flight performance jitters every second. Is there a timer that triggers every second doing a lot of computation?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"severedsolo","CreatedById":80345,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-20T07:43:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224022152\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204404\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221629444928\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Apricot\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Apricot said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis mod makes my in-game flight performance jitters every second. Is there a timer that triggers every second doing a lot of computation?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs this when you are in/your orbit is intersecting the atmosphere or all the time?. 99.9% of the time you shouldn\u0027t notice it as the mod aborts the calculation if there\u0027s nothing worth doing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s probably the garbage collector, I\u0027m doing some not very well optimised things in terms of allocations and Lists right now, because \u0022get it working\u0022 comes before \u0022make it fast\u0022. There\u0027s definitely some optimisation to do, if it\u0027s causing issues I\u0027ll try and clean it up a little for the next release.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Apricot","CreatedById":210807,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-20T08:15:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224022157\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204404\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221629445429\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002280345\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022severedsolo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n33 minutes ago, severedsolo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs this when you are in/your orbit is intersecting the atmosphere or all the time?. 99.9% of the time you shouldn\u0027t notice it as the mod aborts the calculation if there\u0027s nothing worth doing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s probably the garbage collector, I\u0027m doing some not very well optimised things in terms of allocations and Lists right now, because \u0022get it working\u0022 comes before \u0022make it fast\u0022. There\u0027s definitely some optimisation to do, if it\u0027s causing issues I\u0027ll try and clean it up a little for the next release.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have JNSQ and Principia installed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe ship was on\u00A0 a trans-munar injection trajectory, soon will\u00A0entering Mun\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E. Mun perigee was ~20km (principia calculated). I didn\u0027t notice what patched conics looked like.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-08-20T08:16:56Z\u0022 title=\u002208/20/2021 08:16  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 20, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Apricot\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"severedsolo","CreatedById":80345,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-20T08:18:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224022163\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204404\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221629447307\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Apricot\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Apricot said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have JNSQ and Principia installed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe ship was on\u00A0 a trans-munar insertion trajectory, soon will\u00A0entering Mun\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E. Mun perigee was ~20km (principia calculated). I didn\u0027t notice what patched conics looked like.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s definitely some potential for excess GC allocation in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E calcs, thank you for raising it - I\u0027ll try and clean it up a little for the next release. I\u0027ll probably give you the option of increasing the timestep too, which should help. Raised \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/severedsolo/AlarmEnhancements/issues/2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E#2\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-08-20T08:22:37Z\u0022 title=\u002208/20/2021 08:22  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 20, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by severedsolo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"severedsolo","CreatedById":80345,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-21T11:06:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/210807-apricot/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022210807\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/210807-apricot/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Apricot\u003C/a\u003E (and anyone else who might be having performance issues). Can you please try this build: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://1drv.ms/u/s!AtG2PODa0fmwi7g1Ey-jLgLKA0MkGA?e=gwb4F8\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://1drv.ms/u/s!AtG2PODa0fmwi7g1Ey-jLgLKA0MkGA?e=gwb4F8\u003C/a\u003E and see if it helps. (I\u0027ve zipped it so your AV doesn\u0027t freak out, just replace the DLL in the AlarmEnhancements folder with this one).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerdel","CreatedById":211529,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-22T09:40:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ncan I install this mod midgame in career mode?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"severedsolo","CreatedById":80345,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-22T09:51:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224022921\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204404\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221629625205\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211529\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerdel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, Kerdel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ncan I install this mod midgame in career mode?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYep, it won\u0027t work 100% until you\u0027ve upgraded your tracking station and got patched conics, but it won\u0027t break anything being installed mid-save. It doesn\u0027t save any data at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"flart","CreatedById":181486,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-25T18:11:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwith these settings I still have added automatic maneuver alarms\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022MOIMUWF.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002264.00\u0022 height=\u0022663\u0022 width=\u00221036\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/MOIMUWF.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"severedsolo","CreatedById":80345,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-26T05:32:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224024179\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204404\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221629915110\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181486\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022flart\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, flart said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwith these settings I still have added automatic maneuver alarms\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah I missed a setting... sorry about that. Will get a fix out for that today, it\u0027s a simple enough fix.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"severedsolo","CreatedById":80345,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-26T05:50:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually, the feature update is taking a while, so let\u0027s do it now. As I haven\u0027t received any feedback on the performance improvements, I\u0027m going to assume they worked.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EAlarm Enhancements 1.0.2 Released\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nCache the list of Alarms to (hopefully) alleviate the GC stutters that were reported.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nFix Maneuver Alarm setting not being respected.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"woeller","CreatedById":174556,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-28T08:47:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould it be possible to add alarms for labs as they exist in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E? I really miss these in the stock alarm app.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"severedsolo","CreatedById":80345,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-28T10:18:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224025174\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204404\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221630140444\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174556\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022woeller\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, woeller said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould it be possible to add alarms for labs as they exist in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E? I really miss these in the stock alarm app.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can certainly look at it! I\u0027ve never used that feature so what does it do? I\u0027m assuming it\u0027s an alarm for when an experiment has finished processing? (I never use the labs so excuse me if I ask stupid questions)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"woeller","CreatedById":174556,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-28T11:07:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s an alarm based on when a Science Lab where data is processed is full. This depends on the science rate (wich depends on the Kerbal lvl), and the amount of data (which obviously decreases over time).\u003Cbr\u003E\nSo you no longer miss the time to send the science.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022hRxLQLl.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002250.20\u0022 height=\u0022506\u0022 width=\u00221008\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/hRxLQLl.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"severedsolo","CreatedById":80345,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-28T11:23:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224025191\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204404\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221630148827\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174556\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022woeller\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, woeller said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s an alarm based on when a Science Lab where data is processed is full. This depends on the science rate (wich depends on the Kerbal lvl), and the amount of data (which obviously decreases over time).\u003Cbr\u003E\nSo you no longer miss the time to send the science.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks - no promises but I\u0027ll take a look at it. Raised \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/severedsolo/AlarmEnhancements/issues/4\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E#4\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-29T13:17:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/80345-severedsolo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002280345\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/80345-severedsolo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@severedsolo\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Fantastic\u00A0mod, thanks for filling in some of the gaps in the stock alarm system! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you\u0027re taking suggestions: would integration with Transfer Window Planner be in scope for this mod? The stock transfer planner is great but I prefer the configurability that TWP provides, so it\u0027d be nice to be able to add a transfer window from that mod directly into a stock alarm, similar to how it\u0027s already done in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"severedsolo","CreatedById":80345,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-29T14:51:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224025600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204404\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221630243078\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183830\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RealKerbal3x\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, RealKerbal3x said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/80345-severedsolo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002280345\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/80345-severedsolo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@severedsolo\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Fantastic\u00A0mod, thanks for filling in some of the gaps in the stock alarm system! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you\u0027re taking suggestions: would integration with Transfer Window Planner be in scope for this mod? The stock transfer planner is great but I prefer the configurability that TWP provides, so it\u0027d be nice to be able to add a transfer window from that mod directly into a stock alarm, similar to how it\u0027s already done in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat change would probably have to be done within TWP.\u00A0 It\u0027s all rather academic at the moment anyway as I understand TWP doesn\u0027t work in 1.12, but as I understand it TWP adds the alarm to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E, so it would be up to TWP to update itself to add to the Stock Alarm Clock instead.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}